quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  40,78,"Indeed We have sent messengers before thee. Among them are those whom We have recounted unto thee, and among them are those whom We have not recounted unto thee. And it was not for a messenger to bring a sign, save by God’s Leave. So when God’s Command comes, judgment is passed in truth; and those who make false claims will then be losers"
  40,79,"God it is Who made cattle for you, that some of them you may ride and some of them you may eat—"
  40,80,and there are benefits for you therein—and that through them you may attain any need that is in your breasts. And upon them and upon ships are you carried
  40,81,And He shows you His signs. So which of God’s signs do you reject
  40,82,"Have they not journeyed upon the earth and observed how those before them fared in the end? They were more numerous than them, greater than them in strength, and left firmer traces upon the earth. But that which they used to earn availed them not"
  40,83,"And when their messengers brought them clear proofs, they exulted in the knowledge they possessed, and that which they used to mock beset them"
  40,84,"Then, when they saw Our Might, they said, “We believe in God alone, and we disavow that which we used to ascribe as partners unto Him.”"
  40,85,"But their believing benefited them not when they saw Our Might. [That is] the wont of God which has passed among His servants; and the disbelievers were then lost"